ny-cli (3.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Self-hosted scraping via aniwatch npm package (no external API dependency)
  * Parallel server racing with Promise.any() for faster streaming
  * Reduced timeouts for faster responsiveness
  * Published as scoped npm package @anjishnusengupta/ny-cli

 -- Anjishnu Sengupta <itsaemail@duck.com>  Tue, 17 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0000

ny-cli (2.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Unified Continue Watching: CLI and website now share the same history
  * Cloud sync uses main Firestore history field for bidirectional sync
  * Server now fetches malId from API for proper website compatibility
  * All synced entries visible on both nyanime.tech and ny-cli

 -- Anjishnu Sengupta <itsaemail@duck.com>  Sat, 03 Jan 2026 12:00:00 +0000

ny-cli (2.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Cloud sync: Fetch watch history from nyanime.tech website
  * Cloud sync: Push watch history from ny-cli to website
  * Fixed duplicate entries in continue watching list
  * Improved history deduplication with awk
  * Better offline support with pending sync

